Pepon Osorio is a Puerto Rican installation artist based in New York. He originally worked as a social worker before becoming an artist. Osorio creates large-scale installations that often address issues of Latino identity, family, and community. His work frequently incorporates everyday objects and deals with contradictions. Osorio aims to create immersive, provocative spaces that make viewers reflect on their own identities and relationships to society. He has created installations in non-traditional spaces like barbershops and homes. Osorio sees his role as an artist as bridging different sectors of society and provoking change. His installations often reference his Puerto Rican heritage while exploring themes of displacement and finding one's place. Osorio embraces his outsider perspective as an immigrant artist to create work that resonates with others who feel displaced.